# ─── Personal content (the whole point of this repo is the framework, not your content) ───
#
# IMPORTANT: this template ships with atoms/ and wiki/ gitignored so the public framework
# repo stays content-free. In YOUR fork, REMOVE the `atoms/*` and `wiki/*` blocks below —
# atom version history lives in git (the `version:` frontmatter field is just a marker;
# the `pre-commit` hook checks it was bumped before each substantive change), so atoms
# must be tracked for the model to work.

# Raw source materials
raw/*
!raw/README.md
!raw/.gitkeep

# Atoms — REMOVE THIS BLOCK IN YOUR FORK so git can record atom history
atoms/*
!atoms/README.md
!atoms/_template.md
!atoms/.gitkeep

# Compiled wiki pages — REMOVE THIS BLOCK IN YOUR FORK
wiki/*
!wiki/_template.md
!wiki/.gitkeep

# Auto-generated artifacts
index.md
lint-report.md

# Personal notes / analysis (not for the public repo)
GAP-ANALYSIS.md

# ─── Python / OS / editor noise ───
Python/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
.obsidian/
